					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10539637#post-4500003</guid>
				<title>Joke vs. Non-joke</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10539637/scp-4474#post-4500003</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 14 Feb 2020 00:06:11 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>TheSpider22</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>5133874</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I really like this one. In my opinion, Joke SCPs are made specifically to be stupid or funny. With actual ones, I get the horror theme, but the Foundation contains the anomalous. Why wouldn't the anomalous occasionally be stupid or funny, without going across the line? +1 from me</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
